---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy - The National Angle"
  description="How The National Angle handles visitor data and protects reader privacy."
>
  <article class="infoPage">
    <header class="infoHero">
      <div class="signalPills"><span>Privacy</span><span>Minimal data</span><span>No ad tracking</span></div>
      <h1>A publication should not require surveillance</h1>
      <p class="pageDeck">The National Angle is designed to collect as little information about readers as practical.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="infoGrid">
      <section><p class="cardLabel">01</p><h2>Information collected</h2><p>The site does not currently ask visitors to create accounts, submit personal details, or accept advertising cookies. The hosting provider may process standard technical logs, such as IP address, browser information, and request timing, to deliver and protect the website.</p></section>
      <section><p class="cardLabel">02</p><h2>Analytics and cookies</h2><p>No advertising trackers or fingerprinting tools are intentionally used. If audience analytics or a newsletter are added later, this policy will be updated before personal information is collected, and any required consent controls will be provided.</p></section>
      <section><p class="cardLabel">03</p><h2>External links</h2><p>Articles may link to other websites. Those services operate under their own privacy policies, and The National Angle does not control their data practices.</p></section>
      <section><p class="cardLabel">04</p><h2>Policy changes</h2><p>This page may change as the publication adds services. Material changes will be reflected here with clearer details about what is collected and why.</p></section>
    </div>

    <p class="policyDate">Last updated: June 13, 2026</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
